<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 2026</p>

<div class="card">
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Spenso</strong> (“the App”, “we”, “our”, or “us”)
    handles your information when you use the Spenso mobile application.
  </p>
  <p>
    By using Spenso, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    Spenso is designed with a privacy-first approach. We do not collect, store,
    or process personally identifiable information on external servers.
  </p>

  <p>The app may store the following data <strong>locally on your device</strong>:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Notes created by you</li>
    <li>Expenses, bills, and financial records</li>
    <li>Split group and transaction data</li>
    <li>App preferences (settings, reminders, themes)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    This data remains entirely under your control unless you explicitly choose
    to export or share it.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>2. Data Storage and Processing</h2>
  <p>
    All user data is stored locally on your device. Spenso does not transmit,
    upload, or sync your data to external servers by default.
  </p>

  <p>
    If future features (such as backup, cloud sync, or sharing) are introduced,
    you will be clearly informed and asked for consent before any data is transferred.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>3. Permissions</h2>
  <p>Spenso may request certain permissions to function properly:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Notifications:</strong> To send reminders for notes, expenses, and alerts.</li>
    <li><strong>Storage (optional):</strong> To export or back up your data when initiated by you.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These permissions are used strictly for core app functionality and not for tracking,
    profiling, or advertising.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    Spenso does not use third-party advertising networks, analytics tools,
    or tracking SDKs that collect personal data.
  </p>

  <p>
    If third-party services are added in future versions, their usage and data
    handling practices will be disclosed in this policy.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data.
    However, since your data is stored locally, the security of your information
    depends on the security of your device.
  </p>

  <p>
    We recommend using device-level protections such as screen locks,
    encryption, and biometric authentication.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>6. Data Loss and Responsibility</h2>
  <p>
    Spenso is not responsible for any loss of data resulting from device damage,
    loss, theft, system failure, or user actions such as deletion or app uninstallation.
  </p>

  <p>
    Users are encouraged to maintain their own backups where applicable.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Spenso is not intended for use by children under the age of 13.
    We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Any changes will be posted
    on this page with an updated revision date.
  </p>

  <p>
    Continued use of the app after changes indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card">
  <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Spenso shall not be liable
    for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use
    or inability to use the app.
  </p>
</div>

